commit_message:
Fix Evaluation Example

Current evaluation example did not match documentation. Fixed it with an example that will run with the repository as-is and a provided `ckpt` file, and will run even on weak computers.
Models now stored in Google Drive

Update README.md

`in-path` argument is now working (was `in_path`)
Allow style transfer to images of different dimensions (issue #12)
updated requirements to be more specific

Python 3 compatibility

Made print statements and len() calls Python 3 compatible

Implemented piping from and to ffmpeg for increased performance

Best performance is when --batch-size is set to 1

Semi-proper termination of input stream.

There might be a frame loss as big as the batch size in worst case.
Fixed a subprocess mishap and fixed frame losses

If the total amount of frames modulus batch size is zero

Fixed last frame bug

Made python3 friendly

Replaced calls to reduce with calls to functools.reduce()
Replaced map() function with list comprehension
Added shebang to setup.sh file so it can be run as "./setup.sh"

Updated py3 support in other files

Removed check for python2
Added py3 support for evaluate.py and tranform_video.py

Removed references to 'check_version'

No longer need to assert python 2 is running, as code should work with both
python2 and python3.

update to support tensorflow 1.0.0

This change use tool:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/tools/compatibility

Add audio support in video-stylization.
And fix a bug of resolution.
Fix a little in mislinked word README

fix wrong flag name in docs

https://github.com/lengstrom/fast-style-transfer/issues/206

Silent unzip

It makes the unzip faster because usually the shell output is slow
Update code with tf_upgrade_v2 for compatability with 2.0
